android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

manifest_analysis.title:
Service (androidx.work.impl.background.systemjob.SystemJobService) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
Permission: android.permission.BIND_JOB_SERVICE
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Service is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

playstore_details.title: Hodler – Crypto Portfolio, Cryptocurrency Tracker
playstore_details.description:
Track crypto portfolio and cryptocurrency market with Hodler in one place. Check top coin prices, cryptocurrency market, and coin market capitalization. Read crypto news feed and coins news. Set coin price alerts.

Hodler is a simple and fast coin market and crypto portfolio tracker. We don't share or sell your data. Your crypto portfolio only stored on-device.

See cryptocurrency prices and price changes, total market capitalization and 24h volume charts, coin details and advanced charts, crypto news of your favorite coins, and other altcoins including Bitcoin, Ethereum, Ripple, Litecoin, IOTA, Cardano, Stellar, and many more.

Main Features:

• 📊 Track your Crypto portfolio in a single place
• 💸 Monitor all popular coins such as Bitcoin, Ethereum, Ripple, IOTA, and more
• ⭐ Add coins you like to Favorites and to see coin price quickly
• 🌎 Examine market condition on a Global Screen market capitalization and 24h volume charts as well as by filtering and sorting top coins
• 🔎Search any altcoin and token (not only based on Ethereum) by symbol or name from over 4000 available coins
• 👁️ See detailed coin overview and cryptocurrency exchanges
• 📈 View real-time interactive charts of coin price for different time ranges against either popular currencies or Bitcoin
• ⏰ Set Crypto Price Alerts and never miss price changes
• 📰 Stay up-to-date with crypto news from over 20 sources including CoinTelegraph and CoinDesk with an option to read coin news
• 🌘 Amazing Dark Theme
• 💱 Set your preferred currency as default: USD, EUR, GPB, CNY, RUB and many more

If you find Hodler crypto tracker app useful, please feel free to rate app on Google Play and write a review for other users. It will help us to make this app better.

Ask a question, send feedback, suggest a new feature or improvement at alex@hodler.sh. We're happy to get any feedback from you.


—
The Hodler Team
